atermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:1024,&quot;width&quot;:1024,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:680,&quot;bytes&quot;:329654,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:true,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F497aa961-163f-4378-bc56-01f73fdbd1e8_1024x1024.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F497aa961-163f-4378-bc56-01f73fdbd1e8_1024x1024.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F497aa961-163f-4378-bc56-01f73fdbd1e8_1024x1024.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F497aa961-163f-4378-bc56-01f73fdbd1e8_1024x1024.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" fetchpriority="high"></picture></div></a> <polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line><figcaption class="image-caption"> GPT-4 的艺术作品。提示：“一个穿着西装的男人欢快地走向悬崖边缘的漫画”</figcaption></figure></div><p>我们这一代人患有大萧条时期的创伤后应激障碍（PTSD）。在我们的成长岁月中，目睹如此多的经济崩溃是一个划时代的事件，而那些成长经历<a href="https://www.nber.org/system/files/working_papers/w29074/w29074.pdf">往往会留下印记</a>。自那场灾难以来，许多人一直在猜测——预测 2010 年代初的量化宽松将导致恶性通货膨胀，2010 年代中期的加息将导致经济衰退，2010 年代末的扩张将“因旧的经济而消亡”。年龄”，新冠疫情将造成另一场大萧条，等等。这些悲观的预测都没有实现。 2012年左右以来，美国经济不断走强。</p><p>但这并不一定意味着我们现在不会走向衰退。事实上，我们可能是。事实上，情况<em>总是</em>如此，因为宏观经济预测者<a href="https://www.stlouisfed.org/on-the-economy/2023/sep/can-economists-predict-recessions">在提前几个月</a><a href="https://www.imf.org/en/Publications/WP/Issues/2018/03/05/How-Well-Do-Economists-Forecast-Recessions-45672">预测经济衰退方面</a><a href="https://www.philadelphiafed.org/the-economy/macroeconomics/why-are-recessions-so-hard-to-predict-random-shocks-and-business-cycles">非常非常糟糕</a>。对于私营部门、学术界和政府的预测者来说都是如此。无论我们使用什么方法，我们对 6 个月后的经济状况知之甚少，对 9 个月后的经济状况也基本上一无所知。</p><p>不过，很多人不同意这种说法。在金融界和金融媒体中，有很多人认为，利用所谓的<strong>收益率曲线</strong>，可以提前预见经济衰退的到来。当出现所谓的“收益率曲线倒挂”时，预计 6 到 12 个月后就会出现经济衰退。从历史上看，这个指标看起来相当可靠。过去四五次我们出现收益率曲线反转，不久之后就出现了经济衰退（图表上的灰色条）： </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F718ef0f4-1a34-422c-9afd-09f68ce6d32f_1318x450.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F718ef0f4-1a34-422c-9afd-09f68ce6d32f_1318x450.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F718ef0f4-1a34-422c-9afd-09f68ce6d32f_1318x450.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F718ef0f4-1a34-422c-9afd-09f68ce6d32f_1318x450.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F718ef0f4-1a34-422c-9afd-09f68ce6d32f_1318x450.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F718ef0f4-1a34-422c-9afd-09f68ce6d32f_1318x450.png" width="1318" height="450" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/718ef0f4-1a34-422c-9afd-09f68ce6d32f_1318x450.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:450,&quot;width&quot;:1318,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:75042,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F718ef0f4-1a34-422c-9afd-09f68ce6d32f_1318x450.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F718ef0f4-1a34-422c-9afd-09f68ce6d32f_1318x450.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F718ef0f4-1a34-422c-9afd-09f68ce6d32f_1318x450.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F718ef0f4-1a34-422c-9afd-09f68ce6d32f_1318x450.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></figure></div><p>事实上，如果你回到 20 世纪 50 年代，这种模式<a href="https://www.frbsf.org/economic-research/publications/economic-letter/2018/march/economic-forecasts-with-yield-curve/">基本上仍然成立</a>。我们唯一一次从该指标中得到“误报”是在 1966 年。八九分之一的误报（取决于你如何计算）是一个相当不错的记录。</p><p>从图表中您应该注意到的另一件主要事情是，收益率曲线最近出现倒挂。事实上，这种倒挂发生在 2022 年 11 月，距今已有一年多了。因此，最常用的经济衰退即将来临的指标现在已经呈红色闪烁一段时间了。事实上，在我刚刚录制的<a href="https://open.spotify.com/episode/2BM60exgDTfjD8nQYG83Pa">Econ 102 的一集中</a>，资产经理 Itay Vinik 认为经济衰退即将到来，并使用收益率曲线作为他的证据 A。</p><p>在选举年，当国家的命运很可能取决于美国人的经济情绪时，我们是否即将陷入衰退的问题<em>非常</em>重要。</p><p>但事实上，自收益率曲线倒挂以来的 14 个月里，我们还没有看到经济衰退，甚至没有看到任何接近衰退的情况。 《华尔街日报》每月对经济学家进行一次调查，2023 年初，他们给出的一年内经济衰退的可能性超过 60%。截至本月，这一比例已降至 40% 以下： </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fff74c3b1-d035-4440-9046-664613d2a14e_829x663.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fff74c3b1-d035-4440-9046-664613d2a14e_829x663.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fff74c3b1-d035-4440-9046-664613d2a14e_829x663.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fff74c3b1-d035-4440-9046-664613d2a14e_829x663.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fff74c3b1-d035-4440-9046-664613d2a14e_829x663.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fff74c3b1-d035-4440-9046-664613d2a14e_829x663.jpeg" width="829" height="663" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/ff74c3b1-d035-4440-9046-664613d2a14e_829x663.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:663,&quot;width&quot;:829,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:89336,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fff74c3b1-d035-4440-9046-664613d2a14e_829x663.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fff74c3b1-d035-4440-9046-664613d2a14e_829x663.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fff74c3b1-d035-4440-9046-664613d2a14e_829x663.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fff74c3b1-d035-4440-9046-664613d2a14e_829x663.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div><figcaption class="image-caption">资料来源：<a href="https://www.wsj.com/economy/it-wont-be-a-recession-it-will-just-feel-like-one-1919267a">华尔街日报</a></figcaption></figure></div><p>好消息<a href="https://www.bloomberg.com/opinion/articles/2023-12-31/us-economy-2023-will-be-hard-to-top-but-2024-could-do-it?sref=R8NfLgwS">不断从各个方面传来</a>：</p><blockquote><p>美国消费者以一阵<a href="https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2023-12-20/us-consumer-confidence-rises-to-5-month-high-on-better-outlook?srnd=all&amp;embedded-checkout=true">经济好消息</a>结束了2023年……推动情绪改善的最大因素是道琼斯工业平均指数和纳斯达克指数在12月创下历史新高，而标准普尔500指数也即将达到这一水平……</p><p>通货膨胀率大幅下降，尤其是美联储用来制定货币政策的核心<a href="https://x.com/ericwallerstein/status/1737836839074185657?s=20">个人消费</a>支出平减指数……这意味着利率下降的预期，这不仅推动了股价上涨，而且应该有助于推动经济增长。更具功能性的住房市场。最新数据显示，新开工率<a href="https://www.axios.com/2023/12/19/housing-market-inventory-new-home-construction">跃升</a>，部分原因是抵押贷款利率下降……</p><p>随着通胀率下降对实际工资的影响，好消息的连锁效应仍在继续……即使是政治上保守的小企业主，他们<a href="https://www.bloomberg.com/news/newsletters/2023-12-08/for-the-economy-everything-s-been-moving-in-different-directions?embedded-checkout=true">表示经济很糟糕</a>，也表示他们正计划增加工人。</p></blockquote><p>在自 20 世纪 80 年代初以来最大、最长的收益率曲线倒挂 14 个月后发生这种情况，表明该指标存在问题——它并不<em>总是</em>表明经济状况疲软。我想我知道那是什么。但首先，我们来谈谈收益率曲线的基本知识，以及为什么人们认为它应该预测经济衰退。</p><h4> “收益率曲线”到底是什么？它的“倒挂”意味着什么？为什么会预测经济衰退？</h4><p><a href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/does-the-yield-curve-tell-us-a-recession">阅读更多</a></p>; 
Is U.S. industrial policy learning from its mistakes?I hope so, because mistakes are being made. https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/is-us-industrial-policy-learning https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/is-us-industrial-policy-learningNoah Smith Wed, 17 Jan 2024 10:40:01 GMT <div class="captioned-image-container"><figure> <a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb1d3c61e-f2f6-42d7-874a-13bf8e99d871_1024x683.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb1d3c61e-f2f6-42d7-874a-13bf8e99d871_1024x683.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb1d3c61e-f2f6-42d7-874a-13bf8e99d871_1024x683.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb1d3c61e-f2f6-42d7-874a-13bf8e99d871_1024x683.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb1d3c61e-f2f6-42d7-874a-13bf8e99d871_1024x683.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb1d3c61e-f2f6-42d7-874a-13bf8e99d871_1024x683.jpeg" width="704" height="469.5625" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/b1d3c61e-f2f6-42d7-874a-13bf8e99d871_1024x683.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:683,&quot;width&quot;:1024,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:704,&quot;bytes&quot;:115362,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:true,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb1d3c61e-f2f6-42d7-874a-13bf8e99d871_1024x683.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb1d3c61e-f2f6-42d7-874a-13bf8e99d871_1024x683.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb1d3c61e-f2f6-42d7-874a-13bf8e99d871_1024x683.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb1d3c61e-f2f6-42d7-874a-13bf8e99d871_1024x683.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" fetchpriority="high"></picture></div></a> <polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line><figcaption class="image-caption"> <a href="https://www.flickr.com/photos/60576371@N04">rchris7702</a>的“ <a href="https://www.flickr.com/photos/60576371@N04/7315965254">Make Mistakes</a> ”已获得<a href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/2.0/?ref=openverse">CC BY 2.0</a>许可。</figcaption></figure></div><p> 1932 年，罗斯福竞选公职时，决心平息大萧条， <a href="https://publicpolicy.pepperdine.edu/academics/research/faculty-research/new-deal/roosevelt-speeches/fr052232.htm">他承诺实施</a>“大胆、持续的实验”政策。他并不真正知道如何对抗萧条——没有人真正知道如何对抗萧条，因为在以前，对抗萧条和衰退并不是政府所做的事情。罗斯福只是承诺继续尝试，直到找到有效的方法。</p><p>他也确实这么做了。新政的许多政策都是失误，甚至是彻底的失败——试图建立政府批准的垄断以提高企业利润，试图人为地制造农业稀缺以增加农民收入，等等。值得赞扬的是，罗斯福最终放弃了大部分不起作用的方法。罗斯福去世后，最终留下的新政经济方针仅包含他最初方针的几部分；相反，它主要由一路上发现的更成功的想法组成，例如金融监管、社会保障、失业救济和大型基础设施项目。</p><p>同样，美国在第二次世界大战中最终成功的<a href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/book-review-freedoms-forge">战争生产努力</a>也涉及到许多早期的失误，无论是在<a href="https://www.amazon.com/Destructive-Creation-American-Business-Politics/dp/0812248333">私营部门还是公共部门</a>。起初，商船和轰炸机等产品的生产速度极其缓慢，但随着美国企业学会了如何加快生产速度，随着官僚们学会了如何适当支持这些企业，效率得到了数量级的提高，美国成为了武器库。民主。</p><p>这是一个非常重要原则的两个非常重要的例子：新的经济方法需要<em>迭代</em>，积极从错误中学习并进行修正。</p><p>你可能会说，美国目前一直在做类似的事情，转向产业政策。在这一点上，我的感觉是，大多数美国政策制定者和知识分子都认识到——或者至少<a href="https://reason.com/2024/01/07/the-post-neoliberalism-moment/">他们相信</a>——振兴美国制造业很重要。但至于如何做到这一点，没有人真正知道。</p><p>特朗普政府相信，他们可以通过总统的劝告、关税和企业减税来激发制造业复兴。他们失败了；但这样的事情并没有完成。拜登政府保留了关税和减税政策，但增加了另一个主要武器：政府补贴。 IRA、CHIPS 法案和其他一些法案也承诺向公司支付在美国建工厂的费用，并承诺向消费者支付费用以购买这些工厂生产的产品。</p><p>到目前为止，这一举措取得了不同程度的成功。拜登执政期间，工厂建设支出出现爆炸式增长，这样的情况已是多年未见。 </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fab571431-1d80-45e7-9ba9-6dbef997abf8_1318x450.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fab571431-1d80-45e7-9ba9-6dbef997abf8_1318x450.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fab571431-1d80-45e7-9ba9-6dbef997abf8_1318x450.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.a